    • onSaveButtonClick

      public void onSaveButtonClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      This method saves the values in the text fields. When the user interacts with the save button, text will be parsed from the text fields. If text fields are empty or incorrectly formatted, an error message will be displayed. If data are entered without error, a project object will be updated along with the associated parts. The user will then be redirected to the main screen.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent -
      Throws:
      IOException

    • onSearch

      public void onSearch(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      The method searches for existing parts by ID or name. When user enters data in the search field, a partial search function will be ran. If the data is present, the table will display the results. If data is not present, an error message will display.
